Preheat your oven to 200°C. Pop the @diced chicken thigh{210%g} in a #mixing bowl{}.

Halve, then remove the cores from the @bell pepper{1} and @green pepper{1/2} and thinly slice. Add these to the bowl with the chicken. Add half the @honey{7.5%ml}, all the @Mexican style spice mix{1}(add less if you prefer things mild) and a glug of @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix well to combine.

Put a #frying pan{} on high heat. When hot, add the chicken, peppers and any marinade left in the bowl. Lower the heat a little and fry, stirring occasionally, until the chicken is browned and the peppers starting to soften, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> You may need to do this in two batches if your pan isn't large enough.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1/2%can} in a #sieve{}.

Turn the heat to medium-low, stir the @tomato puree{15%g} into the chicken and peppers, then add the mixed beans. Cover with a #lid{} and cook, stirring occasionally, for a further ~{3-4%minutes}. Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Lay a @super soft tortilla with whole wheat{4} on a lightly-oiled #baking tray{} (you may need two). Spoon some of the chicken mixture onto one half of the tortilla, sprinkle on a little cheese, then fold the other half of the tortilla over to enclose the filling (you should have a semi-circle shape). Press down lightly so the tortilla stays put. Repeat with the other tortillas - you should have enough filling for two each.

Drizzle a little @oil{} over the quesadillas, then bake on the top shelf of your oven until browned, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Zest then halve the @lime{1}. In a large #bowl{} mix the remaining @honey{7.5%ml}, a squeeze of lime juice and a glug of @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} and thinly slice. Chop the @medium tomato{2} into 2cm chunks. Add the lettuce and tomato to the dressing, toss to coat.

In a small bowl, mix the @soured cream{75%g} and lime zest. Serve the quesadillas with some salad alongside and drizzle with the zesty soured cream. Enjoy!